In a 1955 letter to The Orlando Sentinel, Hurston made the Supreme Court a request for forced integration, calling his decision in Brown against the school office "an insult rather than an honor for my race".
Residents now say that desegregation of schools, despite being positive in some respects, dilutes Eatonville's cohesion and undermines the confidence of its young people.
