Shortly thereafter, the witness, who at first sight, apparently, had not recognized the actress, saw that Locklear had stopped in a nearby street and had come out of the vehicle.
It was this person who alerted emergency services, because "he was worried about Locklear's life."
When the police patrol arrived, he found the actress sitting inside his vehicle, partially blocking the road.
"She seemed confused," and for this reason the agents led her to a specialist drug and alcohol center to submit her to a test.
According to a police spokesman, the actress proved collaborative and the assumption of excess alcohol was discarded from the outset, although "according to what the officers observed at first, we believe Locklear was under the influence of some drug."
Locklear was arrested with suspicion of driving under the effect of some not better specified substance and was locked up in the local prison around 7:00 p.m., to be released a few hours later.
